A fierce gunbattle between paramilitary troops and renegade tribesmen left eight soldiers dead and 23 others wounded in an insurgency-wracked area of southwestern Pakistan.
Dera Bugti lies about 50 kilometers (30 miles) from Pakistan's main gas field at Sui.
Tribal rebels attacked a paramilitary convoy in restive southwest Pakistan  killing three soldiers and injuring seven others.
The government and tribal forces fought a 16-hour gunbattle in Dera Bugti that officials say left at least eight troops and 22 tribesmen dead.
The tribesmen have set up road blocks and dug trenches along roads into Dera Bugti, a town of about 84,000
